strings: <voice_0x01000CD1><se_low>King Trode: Well it's all right for some, isn't it!?
<voice_0x01000CD2><se_low>King Trode: No doubt King Pavan treated you to plenty of fine food and drink! You lucky toads!
<voice_0x01000CD3><se_low>King Trode: The Princess and I have been waiting, you know! Stuck here outside town! And Medea isn't much for conversation these days, hm!

<voice_0x01000CD5><se_low>Yangus: If only you weren't so...green, eh?
Maybe we could get ya into town
and you could 'ave a drink or somefin'.

<voice_0x01000CD6><se_low>Yangus: I ain't exactly a looker meself.
I know wot it's like to be discrimated against.

<voice_0x01000CD7><se_low>Yangus: ...Oi, guv! I've got an idea.
The town I used to live in ain't too far south of 'ere. How about we 'ead off down there, eh?

<voice_0x01000C65><se_low>Yangus: Sure, Pickham ain't no rose garden, but it's in
the middle o' nowhere, right. Even a strange
old geezer like 'im would fit in no problem.
<voice_0x01000C66><se_low>Yangus: Old Grandad 'ere 'll be able to getta drink!
<voice_0x01000CD8><se_low>Yangus: An' we might get a clue about where that Dhoulmagus 'as got to an' all.
<voice_0x01000CD9><se_low>Yangus: There's a bloke there who knows ev'ryfin' about ev'ryfin'. We call 'im Brains. He's a mate o' mine. He'll know somefin'! Dead cert!

<voice_0x01000CDA><se_low>Yangus: See, two birds wiv one stone, eh!
I ain't just a pretty face! Come on!
Let's get goin' south! Pickham 'ere we come!
